This paper discusses the impact of packet fragmentation on LPWANs, which are wireless networks designed for low-power, long-range communication. The analysis focuses on parameters such as energy consumption, throughput, goodput, and end-to-end delay. Given the focus on wireless networks and communication protocols, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other possible sub-categories include cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper also touches on issues related to reliability, latency, and energy efficiency in distributed systems.
